result.description: Find the factors that contributed the highest net profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT FACTOR FROM title_data ORDER BY NET DESC LIMIT 1

result.description: Find the currencies driving the top-performing portfolios.
result.sql_script: SELECT CUR, PF FROM title_data ORDER BY PROF_LOSS DESC LIMIT 10

result.description: Calculate the average NET and PROF_LOSS for each BUIS by DATE.
result.sql_script: SELECT BUIS, DATE, AVG(NET), AVG(PROF_LOSS) FROM title_data GROUP BY BUIS, DATE

result.description: Find the top 5 BUIS with the highest NET profits
result.sql_script: SELECT BUIS FROM title_data ORDER BY NET DESC LIMIT 5

result.description: Find the bottom 5 BUIS with the lowest NET losses
result.sql_script: SELECT BUIS FROM title_data WHERE PROF_LOSS = 'LOSS' ORDER BY NET ASC LIMIT 5

result.description: Calculate the sum of NET profit/loss for each PF.
result.sql_script: SELECT PF, SUM(NET) FROM title_data GROUP BY PF

result.description: Find the maximum NET profit for each BUIS on each DATE
result.sql_script: SELECT BUIS, DATE, max(NET) FROM title_data GROUP BY BUIS, DATE

result.description: Find the minimum NET loss for each BUIS on each DATE.
result.sql_script: SELECT BUIS, DATE, min(NET) FROM title_data WHERE PROF_LOSS = 'LOSS' GROUP BY BUIS, DATE

result.description: Find the top 5 DSKs with the highest NET profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT DSK FROM title_data ORDER BY NET DESC LIMIT 5

result.description: Find the bottom 5 DSK with the lowest NET profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT DSK FROM title_data ORDER BY NET ASC LIMIT 5

result.description: Calculate the average NET profit/loss for each currency.
result.sql_script: SELECT CUR, AVG(NET) FROM title_data GROUP BY CUR

result.description: Calculate the sum of NET profit/loss for each FACTOR
result.sql_script: SELECT FACTOR, SUM(NET) FROM title_data GROUP BY FACTOR

result.description: Find the top 5 PF with the highest NET profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT PF FROM title_data ORDER BY NET DESC LIMIT 5

result.description: Find the bottom 5 PF with the lowest NET profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT PF FROM title_data ORDER BY NET ASC LIMIT 5

result.description: Calculate the mean NET and PROF_LOSS for each BUIS and DATE combination.
result.sql_script: SELECT BUIS, DATE, AVG(NET), AVG(CASE WHEN PROF_LOSS = 'PROFFIT' THEN 1 WHEN PROF_LOSS = 'LOSS' THEN -1 ELSE 0 END) AS AVG_PROF_LOSS FROM title_data GROUP BY BUIS, DATE

result.description: Calculate average, max, min, sum, and count of NET
result.sql_script: SELECT AVG(NET), MAX(NET), MIN(NET), SUM(NET), COUNT(NET) FROM title_data

result.description: Calculate average, max, min, variance, and sum of PROF_LOSS grouped by BUIS
result.sql_script: SELECT BUIS, AVG(CAST(PROF_LOSS AS REAL)), MAX(CAST(PROF_LOSS AS REAL)), MIN(CAST(PROF_LOSS AS REAL)), SUM(CAST(PROF_LOSS AS REAL)) FROM title_data GROUP BY BUIS

result.description: Calculate average, max, min, variance, and sum of NET profit/loss grouped by currency.
result.sql_script: SELECT CUR, AVG(NET), MAX(NET), MIN(NET), (SUM(NET*NET) - SUM(NET)*SUM(NET)/COUNT(NET))/(COUNT(NET)-1), SUM(NET) FROM title_data GROUP BY CUR

result.description: Calculate average, max, min, variance, and sum of NET profit/loss grouped by top 5 PF portfolios
result.sql_script: WITH PortfolioAverages AS (SELECT PF, AVG(NET) AS avg_net FROM title_data GROUP BY PF), PortfolioCounts AS (SELECT PF, COUNT(*) AS portfolio_count FROM title_data GROUP BY PF ORDER BY portfolio_count DESC LIMIT 5) SELECT td.PF, AVG(td.NET), MAX(td.NET), MIN(td.NET), SUM((td.NET - pa.avg_net) * (td.NET - pa.avg_net)) / (COUNT(td.NET) - 1), SUM(td.NET) FROM title_data td JOIN PortfolioAverages pa ON td.PF = pa.PF JOIN PortfolioCounts pc ON td.PF = pc.PF GROUP BY td.PF

result.description: Calculate average, max, min, variance, and sum of NET profit/loss grouped by bottom 5 PF portfolios
result.sql_script: SELECT PF, AVG(NET), MAX(NET), MIN(NET), SUM(NET), COUNT(NET) FROM title_data GROUP BY PF ORDER BY SUM(NET) ASC LIMIT 5

result.description: calculate average, max, min, variance, and sum of NET profit/loss grouped by top 5 DSK desks
result.sql_script: WITH DeskSummary AS (SELECT DSK, AVG(NET) AS avg_net, MAX(NET) AS max_net, MIN(NET) AS min_net, SUM(NET) AS sum_net, COUNT(NET) AS count_net FROM title_data GROUP BY DSK ORDER BY SUM(NET) DESC LIMIT 5) SELECT DSK, avg_net, max_net, min_net, sum_net, count_net, SUM((title_data.NET - DeskSummary.avg_net) * (title_data.NET - DeskSummary.avg_net)) / DeskSummary.count_net AS variance FROM title_data JOIN DeskSummary ON title_data.DSK = DeskSummary.DSK GROUP BY DSK, avg_net, max_net, min_net, sum_net, count_net ORDER BY sum_net DESC

result.description: Calculate average, max, min, variance, and sum of NET profit/loss grouped by bottom 5 DSK desks
result.sql_script: SELECT AVG(NET), MAX(NET), MIN(NET), SUM(NET), DSK FROM title_data WHERE DSK IN (SELECT DSK FROM title_data GROUP BY DSK ORDER BY SUM(NET) ASC LIMIT 5) GROUP BY DSK

result.description: Calculate the average NET profit/loss for each currency and rank them in descending order.
result.sql_script: SELECT CUR, AVG(NET) AS average_net FROM title_data GROUP BY CUR ORDER BY average_net DESC

result.description: Find the bottom currencies by average NET profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT CUR, AVG(NET) AS Average_NET FROM title_data GROUP BY CUR ORDER BY Average_NET ASC LIMIT 5;

result.description: Counts the number of transactions for each factor.
result.sql_script: SELECT FACTOR, count(*) FROM title_data GROUP BY FACTOR

result.description: Calculate the percentage contribution of each FACTOR to the total profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT FACTOR, (SUM(PROF_LOSS) * 100.0 / (SELECT SUM(PROF_LOSS) FROM title_data)) AS Percentage_Contribution FROM title_data GROUP BY FACTOR

result.description: Calculate the trend of total NET profit/loss over time (daily, monthly, yearly).
result.sql_script: SELECT DATE, sum(NET) FROM title_data GROUP BY DATE ORDER BY DATE

result.description: Calculate the 7-day moving average of NET profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT DATE, AVG(NET) OVER (ORDER BY DATE ASC ROWS BETWEEN 6 PRECEDING AND CURRENT ROW) AS moving_average FROM title_data GROUP BY DATE ORDER BY DATE

result.description: Calculate the standard deviation of NET profit/loss grouped by BUIS
result.sql_script: SELECT BUIS, SUM(NET*NET) - COUNT(NET) * AVG(NET) * AVG(NET) AS stddev_net FROM title_data GROUP BY BUIS

result.description: Calculate the correlation between FACTOR and NET profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT corr(CASE WHEN FACTOR = 'BondBasis' THEN 1 WHEN FACTOR = 'FXDelta' THEN 2 WHEN FACTOR = 'IRDelta' THEN 3 ELSE 0 END, CAST(NET AS REAL)) FROM title_data

result.description: Calculate skewness and kurtosis of NET profit/loss distribution.
result.sql_script:
WITH
  Data AS (
    SELECT
      CAST(NET AS REAL) AS NetValue
    FROM title_data
  ),
  Calculations AS (
    SELECT
      (SUM(NetValue)) AS SumX,
      SUM(NetValue * NetValue) AS SumX2,
      SUM(NetValue * NetValue * NetValue) AS SumX3,
      SUM(NetValue * NetValue * NetValue * NetValue) AS SumX4,
      COUNT(NetValue) AS N,
      AVG(NetValue) AS Average
    FROM Data
  ),
  StdDev AS (
    SELECT
      SQRT(SUMX2 / N - Average * Average) AS StandardDeviation
    FROM Calculations
  ),
  Skewness AS (
    SELECT
      (
        (SUMX3 / (SELECT N FROM Calculations)) - 3 * (SELECT Average FROM Calculations) * (SUMX2 / (SELECT N FROM Calculations)) + 2 * POWER((SELECT Average FROM Calculations), 3)
      ) / POWER((SELECT StandardDeviation FROM StdDev), 3) AS Skew
    FROM Calculations
  ),
  Kurtosis AS (
    SELECT
      (
        (SUMX4 / (SELECT N FROM Calculations)) - 4 * (SELECT Average FROM Calculations) * (SUMX3 / (SELECT N FROM Calculations)) + 6 * POWER((SELECT Average FROM Calculations), 2) * (SUMX2 / (SELECT N FROM Calculations)) - 3 * POWER((SELECT Average FROM Calculations), 4)
      ) / POWER((SELECT StandardDeviation FROM StdDev), 4) - 3 AS Kurt
    FROM Calculations
  )
SELECT
  Skew AS skewness,
  Kurt AS kurtosis
FROM Skewness, Kurtosis

result.description: Calculate the standard deviation of NET for each PF portfolio and then find the portfolios with the highest standard deviation.
result.sql_script: SELECT PF, SUM(NET * NET) - COUNT(NET) * AVG(NET) * AVG(NET) AS stddev_net FROM title_data GROUP BY PF ORDER BY stddev_net DESC

result.description: Calculate the variance of NET for each DSK and order by variance in descending order to find the desks with the highest variance.
result.sql_script: SELECT DSK, SUM(NET * NET) - SUM(NET) * SUM(NET) / COUNT(NET) AS variance FROM title_data GROUP BY DSK ORDER BY variance DESC

result.description: Calculate the probability distribution of NET profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT NET, PROF_LOSS, COUNT(*) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM title_data) AS probability FROM title_data GROUP BY NET, PROF_LOSS ORDER BY NET, PROF_LOSS

result.description: Calculate the cumulative sum of NET profit/loss over time.
result.sql_script: SELECT DATE, SUM(NET) OVER (ORDER BY DATE) AS cumulative_net FROM title_data ORDER BY DATE

result.description: Find the currency with the most volatile NET profit/loss.
result.sql_script: SELECT CUR FROM title_data GROUP BY CUR ORDER BY SUM((NET - AVG(NET)) * (NET - AVG(NET))) DESC LIMIT 1

result.description: Ratio of profitable to loss-making transactions per FACTOR
result.sql_script: SELECT FACTOR, CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN PROF_LOSS = 'PROFFIT' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / SUM(CASE WHEN PROF_LOSS = 'LOSS' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Profit_Loss_Ratio FROM title_data GROUP BY FACTOR

result.description: Calculate the average profit/loss for each portfolio and then calculate the variance of the profit/loss for each portfolio.  Finally, sort by the variance in ascending order to find the portfolios with the most consistently positive profits.
result.sql_script: SELECT PF, AVG(CAST(REPLACE(PROF_LOSS, 'PROFFIT', '1') AS REAL)) AS avg_profit,SUM((CAST(REPLACE(PROF_LOSS, 'PROFFIT', '1') AS REAL) - AVG(CAST(REPLACE(PROF_LOSS, 'PROFFIT', '1') AS REAL)) OVER (PARTITION BY PF)) * (CAST(REPLACE(PROF_LOSS, 'PROFFIT', '1') AS REAL) - AVG(CAST(REPLACE(PROF_LOSS, 'PROFFIT', '1') AS REAL)) OVER (PARTITION BY PF))) / COUNT(*) AS variance FROM title_data GROUP BY PF ORDER BY variance ASC

result.description: Find the factor that contributes most to the total profit/loss variance.
result.sql_script: SELECT FACTOR, SUM(PROF_LOSS) FROM title_data GROUP BY FACTOR ORDER BY ABS(SUM(PROF_LOSS)) DESC LIMIT 1

result.description: Calculate the ratio of profit to loss per DSK desk.
result.sql_script: SELECT DSK, SUM(CASE WHEN PROF_LOSS = 'PROFFIT' THEN NET ELSE 0 END) * 1.0 / SUM(CASE WHEN PROF_LOSS = 'LOSS' THEN NET ELSE 0 END) AS profit_loss_ratio FROM title_data GROUP BY DSK

result.description: Find the currency with the highest total profit.
result.sql_script: SELECT CUR, SUM(PROF_LOSS) AS TOTAL_PROFIT FROM title_data WHERE PROF_LOSS > 0 GROUP BY CUR ORDER BY TOTAL_PROFIT DESC LIMIT 1;

result.description: Find the factor with the highest frequency of losses.
result.sql_script: SELECT FACTOR FROM title_data WHERE PROF_LOSS = 'LOSS' GROUP BY FACTOR ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1;
